2026-02-21 14:48:28 - INFO - 716 -{"tools": [], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "Travel Planner: Create day-by-day itinerary with activities, hotel options (budget/mid/luxury + prices), and budget breakdown (accommodation, food, transport, attractions, total).", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "I want to two day trip to goa with the budget of 50000. Can you help me plan it?"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-399acd96-5592-4920-9345-4922d0eed9fa", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "stop", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway \u2013\u202f\u20b9\u202f50,000 (INR)  \n**Travel dates:** Choose any weekend or short\u2011holiday window (e.g.,\u202fFriday\u202f\u2192\u202fSunday).  \n**Assumption:** You are travelling from a major Indian city (e.g., Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore) and will fly to Goa. If you prefer train/bus, the numbers can be adjusted downwards.\n\n---\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK\u2011LOOK BUDGET SUMMARY  \n\n| Category | Budget\u2011Friendly (2\u202fnights) | Mid\u2011Range (2\u202fnights) | Luxury (2\u202fnights) |\n|----------|----------------------------|----------------------|-------------------|\n| **Flights (round\u2011trip)** | \u20b9\u202f6,000 \u2013 8,000 | \u20b9\u202f6,000 \u2013 8,000 | \u20b9\u202f6,000 \u2013 8,000 |\n| **Accommodation** | \u20b9\u202f2,500\u202f/\u202fnight \u2192 \u20b9\u202f5,000 | \u20b9\u202f5,500\u202f/\u202fnight \u2192 \u20b9\u202f11,000 | \u20b9\u202f12,000\u202f/\u202fnight \u2192 \u20b9\u202f24,000 |\n| **Local transport** (airport\u2011to\u2011hotel, taxis, scooters) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 | \u20b9\u202f2,500 | \u20b9\u202f3,500 |\n| **Food & drinks** (breakfast, lunch, dinner, snacks) | \u20b9\u202f1,200\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 \u20b9\u202f2,400 | \u20b9\u202f2,000\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 \u20b9\u202f4,000 | \u20b9\u202f3,500\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| **Attractions & activities** (entry fees, water\u2011sports, tours) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 | \u20b9\u202f3,500 | \u20b9\u202f5,000 |\n| **Misc. (souvenirs, tips, emergency)\u200b** | \u20b9\u202f1,000 | \u20b9\u202f1,500 | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| **Total (approx.)** | **\u20b9\u202f18,400 \u2013 20,900** | **\u20b9\u202f30,500 \u2013 33,500** | **\u20b9\u202f48,000 \u2013 51,500** |\n\n> **Bottom line:**  \n> \u2022 If you stay in the **budget** or **mid\u2011range** segment you\u2019ll comfortably stay **well under \u20b9\u202f50,000**.  \n> \u2022 The **luxury** option pushes the total just a little above the target; you can trim a few activities or choose a slightly cheaper boutique hotel to stay inside the limit.\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### Day\u202f1 \u2013 Arrival, North Goa Highlights  \n| Time | Activity | Cost (per person) | Notes |\n|------|----------|-------------------|-------|\n| **07:00 \u2013 09:00** | Flight to Goa (e.g., Mumbai\u2011Goa) | \u20b9\u202f3,000 \u2013 4,000 (one\u2011way) | Book early\u2011bird or low\u2011cost carrier (IndiGo, SpiceJet). |\n| **09:30 \u2013 10:30** | Airport \u2192 Hotel transfer (pre\u2011booked taxi or app\u2011cab) | \u20b9\u202f500 \u2013 800 | Most hotels offer a pick\u2011up service for a small fee. |\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:30** | Check\u2011in, freshen up & brunch at **Caf\u00e9 Bodega** (Calangute) | \u20b9\u202f300 \u2013 500 | Light Goan\u2011style breakfast (p\u00e3o\u202fbiscuit, fresh juice). |\n| **12:45 \u2013 15:00** | **Calangute \u2192 Baga Beach** \u2013 sun, swim, optional water\u2011sport (parasailing) | Parasailing \u20b9\u202f800 (optional) | Walk along the shoreline; rent a beach chair for \u20b9\u202f150. |\n| **15:30 \u2013 17:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** (entry free) | Free | Great photo\u2011ops; small parking fee \u20b9\u202f50 if you drive. |\n| **18:00 \u2013 19:30** | Sunset at **Candolim Beach** \u2013 relax with a coconut water | \u20b9\u202f100 \u2013 150 | |\n| **20:00 \u2013 22:00** | Dinner at **Mum\u2019s Kitchen** (authentic Goan cuisine) | \u20b9\u202f600 \u2013 800 | Try fish curry, pork vindaloo, bebinca. |\n| **22:30** | Return to hotel \u2013 early night or explore Calangute night market (optional) | \u2013 | |\n\n**Accommodation suggestions (2\u2011night stay)**  \n\n| Category | Hotel (2\u202fnights) | Approx. price/night | Amenities |\n|----------|------------------|---------------------|-----------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa \u2013 Guesthouse** (Calangute) | \u20b9\u202f2,500 | Free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop, near beach, shared bathroom (some rooms private). |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim) | \u20b9\u202f5,500 | Air\u2011cond, pool, breakfast included, 5\u2011min walk to beach. |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim) | \u20b9\u202f12,000 | 5\u2011star beachfront, multiple restaurants, spa, private beach. |\n\n---\n\n### Day\u202f2 \u2013 South Goa Exploration & Departure  \n\n| Time | Activity | Cost (per person) | Notes |\n|------|----------|-------------------|-------|\n| **07:30 \u2013 08:30** | Breakfast at hotel (included in mid\u2011lux) or at **Anandashram** (budget) | \u20b9\u202f150 \u2013 250 | Try Goan poee & tea. |\n| **09:00 \u2013 11:30** | **Old Goa Churches** \u2013 Basilica of Bom\u202fBom, Se\u202fCathedral, Church of St\u202fFrancis of Assisi | Entry free; donation optional | Hire a **scooter** (\u20b9\u202f350\u202f/\u202fday) or book a **guided half\u2011day tour** (\u20b9\u202f1,200). |\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | Lunch at **Martin\u2019s Corner** (Betalbatim) \u2013 famous for seafood | \u20b9\u202f600 \u2013 900 | Must\u2011try: kingfish pepper fry, prawn balch\u00e3o. |\n| **14:00 \u2013 15:30** | **Colva Beach** \u2013 relax, optional dolphin\u2011watching boat (\u20b9\u202f1,200) | \u2013 | |\n| **16:00 \u2013 17:30** | **Palolem Beach** \u2013 sunset & beach\u2011side cocktail (optional) | Cocktail \u20b9\u202f250 | If you\u2019re short on time, skip Palolem and head straight to the airport. |\n| **18:00 \u2013 19:00** | Return to hotel, collect luggage | \u2013 | |\n| **19:30 \u2013 20:30** | Transfer to Goa International Airport (taxi or pre\u2011booked shuttle) | \u20b9\u202f500 \u2013 800 | |\n| **21:30 \u2013 23:30** | Flight back home | \u20b9\u202f3,000 \u2013 4,000 (one\u2011way) | |\n\n**Alternative \u201cRelax\u2011Only\u201d version (if you prefer less travel):**  \n- Skip Old Goa and stay on the beach.  \n- Use the second day for a **spa** (\u20b9\u202f2,000) and a **sunset cruise** (\u20b9\u202f1,500).  \n- This keeps the total within the same budget range.\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED BUDGET BREAKDOWN (per person)\n\n### A. Budget\u2011Friendly Option  \n| Item | Cost (INR) |\n|------|------------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Accommodation (Casa De Goa) | \u20b9\u202f5,000 |\n| Local transport (airport\u2011taxi + scooter) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| Food & drinks | \u20b9\u202f2,400 |\n| Attractions (parasailing, dolphin\u2011watch, entry donations) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f1,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f19,400** |\n\n### B. Mid\u2011Range Option  \n| Item | Cost (INR) |\n|------|------------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Accommodation (The Flora Residency) | \u20b9\u202f11,000 |\n| Local transport (airport\u2011taxi + scooter + occasional cab) | \u20b9\u202f2,500 |\n| Food & drinks | \u20b9\u202f4,000 |\n| Attractions (guided Old\u2011Goa tour, water\u2011sports) | \u20b9\u202f3,500 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f1,500 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f29,500** |\n\n### C. Luxury Option  \n| Item | Cost (INR) |\n|------|------------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Accommodation (Taj Exotica) | \u20b9\u202f24,000 |\n| Local transport (airport\u2011taxi + private car) | \u20b9\u202f3,500 |\n| Food & drinks (restaurant meals, cocktails) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Attractions (private guided tour, premium water\u2011sports) | \u20b9\u202f5,000 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f48,500** |\n\n> **Tip:** All figures are **per adult**. If you travel with a partner, double the accommodation, food, and transport costs, but the flight cost stays the same per ticket.\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TIPS & QUICK CHECK\u2011LIST  \n\n| Tip | Why it matters |\n|-----|----------------|\n| **Book flights & hotels 3\u20114\u202fweeks in advance** | Prices drop sharply; you\u2019ll lock in the budget\u2011friendly rates. |\n| **Use a scooter for local travel** | \u20b9\u202f350\u202f/\u202fday is the cheapest way to zip between beaches and attractions. |\n| **Carry cash for small vendors** | Many beach shacks and local markets prefer cash (\u20b9\u202f10\u2011\u20b9\u202f500 notes). |\n| **Stay hydrated & apply sunscreen** | Goa sun can be intense, especially on the beach. |\n| **Respect church dress codes** | In Old Goa, shoulders and knees should be covered. |\n| **Check the monsoon calendar** | June\u2011September is rainy; best to travel Oct\u2011May for sunshine. |\n| **Travel insurance** (\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f500\u2011\u20b9\u202f1,000) | Small price for peace of mind in case of flight delays or medical needs. |\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK\u2011START ACTION PLAN  \n\n1. **Pick your dates** \u2013 look for a Friday\u2011Sunday slot with cheap flights.  \n2. **Reserve flights** \u2013 use Skyscanner/MakeMyTrip; set price alerts.  \n3. **Choose accommodation** \u2013 book via Booking.com or directly on the hotel website (often a 5\u201110\u202f% discount).  \n4. **Pre\u2011book airport transfer** \u2013 many hotels offer a pick\u2011up service for a fixed fee.  \n5. **Reserve any water\u2011sports** you definitely want (parasailing, dolphin\u2011watch) \u2013 they fill up fast in peak season.  \n6. **Create a packing list** \u2013 swimwear, flip\u2011flops, light cottons, a light jacket for evenings, sunscreen, reusable water bottle.  \n\n---\n\n### \ud83c\udf89 Ready to go?  \n\nIf you\u2019d like a **customized version** (e.g., vegetarian\u2011friendly restaurants, family\u2011friendly activities, or a focus on nightlife), just let me know and I\u2019ll tweak the plan accordingly! Safe travels and enjoy the sun\u2011kissed sands of Goa.", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": null, "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": null, "reasoning": "We need to produce a day-by-day itinerary for a two-day trip to Goa, with budget of 50,000 (presumably INR). Provide activities, hotel options (budget/mid/luxury with prices), and budget breakdown (accommodation, food, transport, attractions, total). Should be helpful. Provide suggestions for transport (flight/train, local transport). Provide cost estimates. Also maybe include tips. Use Indian rupees. Provide a table. Ensure total within 50k. Provide three hotel categories with per night cost. Provide total cost for each category. Provide day-wise schedule. Let's craft."}}], "created": 1771665508, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "on_demand", "system_fingerprint": "fp_e10890e4b9", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 2609, "prompt_tokens": 137, "total_tokens": 2746, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 124, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": null, "queue_time": 0.046285219, "prompt_time": 0.006741031, "completion_time": 5.618065854, "total_time": 5.624806885}, "usage_breakdown": null, "x_groq": {"id": "req_01khzqwckdedy9xb2cd35173sp", "seed": 2063577582}}, "prompt_tokens": 137, "completion_tokens": 2609, "agent_id": "Travel_Planner_54a6adbe-5f24-4859-90f0-fb551ddaf614/54a6adbe-5f24-4859-90f0-fb551ddaf614"}
2026-02-21 14:48:28 - INFO - 405 -Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': TextMessage(id='c915a170-f672-4f31-8064-c738691cb462', source='Travel_Planner', models_usage=RequestUsage(prompt_tokens=137, completion_tokens=2609), metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 2, 21, 9, 18, 28, 662123, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content='## 2\u2011Day Goa Getaway –\u202f\u20b9\u202f50,000 (INR)  \n**Travel dates:** Choose any weekend or short\u2011holiday window (e.g.,\u202fFriday\u202f\u2192\u202fSunday).  \n**Assumption:** You are travelling from a major Indian city (e.g., Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore) and will fly to Goa. If you prefer train/bus, the numbers can be adjusted downwards.\n\n---\n\n### 1\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK\u2011LOOK BUDGET SUMMARY  \n\n| Category | Budget\u2011Friendly (2\u202fnights) | Mid\u2011Range (2\u202fnights) | Luxury (2\u202fnights) |\n|----------|----------------------------|----------------------|-------------------|\n| **Flights (round\u2011trip)** | \u20b9\u202f6,000 – 8,000 | \u20b9\u202f6,000 – 8,000 | \u20b9\u202f6,000 – 8,000 |\n| **Accommodation** | \u20b9\u202f2,500\u202f/\u202fnight \u2192 \u20b9\u202f5,000 | \u20b9\u202f5,500\u202f/\u202fnight \u2192 \u20b9\u202f11,000 | \u20b9\u202f12,000\u202f/\u202fnight \u2192 \u20b9\u202f24,000 |\n| **Local transport** (airport\u2011to\u2011hotel, taxis, scooters) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 | \u20b9\u202f2,500 | \u20b9\u202f3,500 |\n| **Food & drinks** (breakfast, lunch, dinner, snacks) | \u20b9\u202f1,200\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 \u20b9\u202f2,400 | \u20b9\u202f2,000\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 \u20b9\u202f4,000 | \u20b9\u202f3,500\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| **Attractions & activities** (entry fees, water\u2011sports, tours) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 | \u20b9\u202f3,500 | \u20b9\u202f5,000 |\n| **Misc. (souvenirs, tips, emergency)\u200b** | \u20b9\u202f1,000 | \u20b9\u202f1,500 | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| **Total (approx.)** | **\u20b9\u202f18,400 – 20,900** | **\u20b9\u202f30,500 – 33,500** | **\u20b9\u202f48,000 – 51,500** |\n\n> **Bottom line:**  \n> • If you stay in the **budget** or **mid\u2011range** segment you’ll comfortably stay **well under \u20b9\u202f50,000**.  \n> • The **luxury** option pushes the total just a little above the target; you can trim a few activities or choose a slightly cheaper boutique hotel to stay inside the limit.\n\n---\n\n## 2\ufe0f\u20e3 DAY\u2011BY\u2011DAY ITINERARY  \n\n### Day\u202f1 – Arrival, North Goa Highlights  \n| Time | Activity | Cost (per person) | Notes |\n|------|----------|-------------------|-------|\n| **07:00 – 09:00** | Flight to Goa (e.g., Mumbai\u2011Goa) | \u20b9\u202f3,000 – 4,000 (one\u2011way) | Book early\u2011bird or low\u2011cost carrier (IndiGo, SpiceJet). |\n| **09:30 – 10:30** | Airport \u2192 Hotel transfer (pre\u2011booked taxi or app\u2011cab) | \u20b9\u202f500 – 800 | Most hotels offer a pick\u2011up service for a small fee. |\n| **10:30 – 12:30** | Check\u2011in, freshen up & brunch at **Café Bodega** (Calangute) | \u20b9\u202f300 – 500 | Light Goan\u2011style breakfast (păo\u202fbiscuit, fresh juice). |\n| **12:45 – 15:00** | **Calangute \u2192 Baga Beach** – sun, swim, optional water\u2011sport (parasailing) | Parasailing \u20b9\u202f800 (optional) | Walk along the shoreline; rent a beach chair for \u20b9\u202f150. |\n| **15:30 – 17:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** (entry free) | Free | Great photo\u2011ops; small parking fee \u20b9\u202f50 if you drive. |\n| **18:00 – 19:30** | Sunset at **Candolim Beach** – relax with a coconut water | \u20b9\u202f100 – 150 | |\n| **20:00 – 22:00** | Dinner at **Mum’s Kitchen** (authentic Goan cuisine) | \u20b9\u202f600 – 800 | Try fish curry, pork vindaloo, bebinca. |\n| **22:30** | Return to hotel – early night or explore Calangute night market (optional) | – | |\n\n**Accommodation suggestions (2\u2011night stay)**  \n\n| Category | Hotel (2\u202fnights) | Approx. price/night | Amenities |\n|----------|------------------|---------------------|-----------|\n| **Budget** | **Casa De Goa – Guesthouse** (Calangute) | \u20b9\u202f2,500 | Free Wi\u2011Fi, rooftop, near beach, shared bathroom (some rooms private). |\n| **Mid\u2011Range** | **The Flora Residency** (Candolim) | \u20b9\u202f5,500 | Air\u2011cond, pool, breakfast included, 5\u2011min walk to beach. |\n| **Luxury** | **Taj Exotica Resort & Spa** (Benaulim) | \u20b9\u202f12,000 | 5\u2011star beachfront, multiple restaurants, spa, private beach. |\n\n---\n\n### Day\u202f2 – South Goa Exploration & Departure  \n\n| Time | Activity | Cost (per person) | Notes |\n|------|----------|-------------------|-------|\n| **07:30 – 08:30** | Breakfast at hotel (included in mid\u2011lux) or at **Anandashram** (budget) | \u20b9\u202f150 – 250 | Try Goan poee & tea. |\n| **09:00 – 11:30** | **Old Goa Churches** – Basilica of Bom\u202fBom, Se\u202fCathedral, Church of St\u202fFrancis of Assisi | Entry free; donation optional | Hire a **scooter** (\u20b9\u202f350\u202f/\u202fday) or book a **guided half\u2011day tour** (\u20b9\u202f1,200). |\n| **12:00 – 13:30** | Lunch at **Martin’s Corner** (Betalbatim) – famous for seafood | \u20b9\u202f600 – 900 | Must\u2011try: kingfish pepper fry, prawn balchăo. |\n| **14:00 – 15:30** | **Colva Beach** – relax, optional dolphin\u2011watching boat (\u20b9\u202f1,200) | – | |\n| **16:00 – 17:30** | **Palolem Beach** – sunset & beach\u2011side cocktail (optional) | Cocktail \u20b9\u202f250 | If you’re short on time, skip Palolem and head straight to the airport. |\n| **18:00 – 19:00** | Return to hotel, collect luggage | – | |\n| **19:30 – 20:30** | Transfer to Goa International Airport (taxi or pre\u2011booked shuttle) | \u20b9\u202f500 – 800 | |\n| **21:30 – 23:30** | Flight back home | \u20b9\u202f3,000 – 4,000 (one\u2011way) | |\n\n**Alternative “Relax\u2011Only” version (if you prefer less travel):**  \n- Skip Old Goa and stay on the beach.  \n- Use the second day for a **spa** (\u20b9\u202f2,000) and a **sunset cruise** (\u20b9\u202f1,500).  \n- This keeps the total within the same budget range.\n\n---\n\n## 3\ufe0f\u20e3 DETAILED BUDGET BREAKDOWN (per person)\n\n### A. Budget\u2011Friendly Option  \n| Item | Cost (INR) |\n|------|------------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Accommodation (Casa De Goa) | \u20b9\u202f5,000 |\n| Local transport (airport\u2011taxi + scooter) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| Food & drinks | \u20b9\u202f2,400 |\n| Attractions (parasailing, dolphin\u2011watch, entry donations) | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f1,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f19,400** |\n\n### B. Mid\u2011Range Option  \n| Item | Cost (INR) |\n|------|------------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Accommodation (The Flora Residency) | \u20b9\u202f11,000 |\n| Local transport (airport\u2011taxi + scooter + occasional cab) | \u20b9\u202f2,500 |\n| Food & drinks | \u20b9\u202f4,000 |\n| Attractions (guided Old\u2011Goa tour, water\u2011sports) | \u20b9\u202f3,500 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f1,500 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f29,500** |\n\n### C. Luxury Option  \n| Item | Cost (INR) |\n|------|------------|\n| Flights (round\u2011trip) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Accommodation (Taj Exotica) | \u20b9\u202f24,000 |\n| Local transport (airport\u2011taxi + private car) | \u20b9\u202f3,500 |\n| Food & drinks (restaurant meals, cocktails) | \u20b9\u202f7,000 |\n| Attractions (private guided tour, premium water\u2011sports) | \u20b9\u202f5,000 |\n| Miscellaneous | \u20b9\u202f2,000 |\n| **Total** | **\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f48,500** |\n\n> **Tip:** All figures are **per adult**. If you travel with a partner, double the accommodation, food, and transport costs, but the flight cost stays the same per ticket.\n\n---\n\n## 4\ufe0f\u20e3 PRACTICAL TIPS & QUICK CHECK\u2011LIST  \n\n| Tip | Why it matters |\n|-----|----------------|\n| **Book flights & hotels 3\u20114\u202fweeks in advance** | Prices drop sharply; you’ll lock in the budget\u2011friendly rates. |\n| **Use a scooter for local travel** | \u20b9\u202f350\u202f/\u202fday is the cheapest way to zip between beaches and attractions. |\n| **Carry cash for small vendors** | Many beach shacks and local markets prefer cash (\u20b9\u202f10\u2011\u20b9\u202f500 notes). |\n| **Stay hydrated & apply sunscreen** | Goa sun can be intense, especially on the beach. |\n| **Respect church dress codes** | In Old Goa, shoulders and knees should be covered. |\n| **Check the monsoon calendar** | June\u2011September is rainy; best to travel Oct\u2011May for sunshine. |\n| **Travel insurance** (\u2248\u202f\u20b9\u202f500\u2011\u20b9\u202f1,000) | Small price for peace of mind in case of flight delays or medical needs. |\n\n---\n\n## 5\ufe0f\u20e3 QUICK\u2011START ACTION PLAN  \n\n1. **Pick your dates** – look for a Friday\u2011Sunday slot with cheap flights.  \n2. **Reserve flights** – use Skyscanner/MakeMyTrip; set price alerts.  \n3. **Choose accommodation** – book via Booking.com or directly on the hotel website (often a 5\u201110\u202f% discount).  \n4. **Pre\u2011book airport transfer** – many hotels offer a pick\u2011up service for a fixed fee.  \n5. **Reserve any water\u2011sports** you definitely want (parasailing, dolphin\u2011watch) – they fill up fast in peak season.  \n6. **Create a packing list** – swimwear, flip\u2011flops, light cottons, a light jacket for evenings, sunscreen, reusable water bottle.  \n\n---\n\n### \U0001f389 Ready to go?  \n\nIf you’d like a **customized version** (e.g., vegetarian\u2011friendly restaurants, family\u2011friendly activities, or a focus on nightlife), just let me know and I’ll tweak the plan accordingly! Safe travels and enjoy the sun\u2011kissed sands of Goa.', type='TextMessage')}
